	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Does anyone know where to find documentation on the BPS file format?<br /><br /><a href="https://byuu.org/tool/beat/" class="postlink">byuu's official page</a> doesn't have anything for download, not the executable, not the source, and no format documentation.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.romhacking.net/utilities/893/" class="postlink">RHDN</a> has a mirror of an old version, but just the executable, no source.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.smwcentral.net/?p=section&amp;a=details&amp;id=11474" class="postlink">Floating IPS</a> is another utility that can build BPS files, with source code, but no format documentation.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.romhacking.net/utilities/1365/" class="postlink">RomPatcher.js</a> also implements BPS patching, again with source but no format documentation.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


